The final day of Robert Blake's defense case featured his daughter, Delinah Blake-Hurwitz, testifying about adopting Rosie, a child he loved.
Witnesses described his anxiety over Bakley's pregnancy and desire to keep Rosie away from her.
Blake, 71, did not testify but shared his story in a video interview.
Prosecutors argued he killed Bakley due to her con artist ways.
Defense highlighted lack of evidence linking Blake to the murder.
The trial included comedic moments and bizarre testimonies, painting a picture of a complex and troubled Hollywood figure on trial for a heinous crime.
